## State transitions

```
INIT  →  MAP        on: context loaded
MAP   →  REDUCE     on: all workers complete
REDUCE → CORRECTION on: uncertain fields detected
CORRECTION → REDUCE on: correction workers complete
REDUCE → COMPLETE   on: all fields resolved or max attempts reached
```

---

## Error reference

| condition | detected by | action |
|-----------|-------------|--------|
| worker: uncertain | collector | flag in fact_pool |
| worker: unverified citation | main agent | flag in schema |
| max correction attempts | harness | status: requires_review |
| schema structure invalid | validator | raise validation error |
| intersection query A∩B | main agent | run A first, pipe into B |
| article not found | opensearch client | log, skip segment |

---

## Article overlap strategy

B1∩B2 and B1∩B2∩B3 overlaps are expected in WILL documents (bequests, residuary, trust provisions). Strategy:

```
router assigns same article to multiple workers
harness deduplicates before fetching
article fetched ONCE → cached
multiple workers read from cache
different workers cite different passages from same article
```

